<!-- What the Smart Screen Shows -->
<section class="sec bg-slate-50 relative py-16">
 <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6">
 <h2 class="text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic tracking-tighter mb-4 text-center">What Does the <span class="text-brandOrange">Smart Display</span> Show?</h2>
 <p class="text-center text-slate-500 text-sm max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-12">Is a power bank with a display worth it? For your customers, yes — real-time charging data eliminates uncertainty and builds trust. Here's what WOWOHCOOL TFT screens display:</p>

 <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6 max-w-5xl mx-auto">
 <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-200 shadow-sm">
 <h3 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-3 text-sm">Battery Percentage</h3>
 <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">Precise 1% increments (not 4-LED guesswork). Users know exactly when to recharge — reducing "dead battery" anxiety.</p>
 </div>
 <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-200 shadow-sm">
 <h3 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-3 text-sm">Real-Time Wattage (W)</h3>
 <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">Shows actual charging power in watts. Users can verify their device is receiving fast charge speeds (e.g., "22.5W" not slow 5W).</p>
 </div>
 <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-200 shadow-sm">
 <h3 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-3 text-sm">Voltage &amp; Current (V/A)</h3>
 <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">Technical data for power users and tech reviewers. Differentiates your product from "mystery" chargers with no feedback.</p>
 </div>
 <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-200 shadow-sm">
 <h3 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-3 text-sm">Estimated Time Remaining</h3>
 <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">Shows hours/minutes until full charge or empty. Customers plan their day without guessing — fewer 1-star "died too fast" reviews.</p>
 </div>
 <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-200 shadow-sm">
 <h3 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-3 text-sm">Active Port Indicators</h3>
 <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">Visual feedback showing which ports are active and at what speed. No confusion about whether the cable is connected properly.</p>
 </div>
 <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-200 shadow-sm">
 <h3 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-3 text-sm">Auto-Dim &amp; Low Power</h3>
 <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">Display auto-dims after 10 seconds, consuming less than 0.1% battery per hour. The screen doesn't meaningfully affect runtime.</p>
 </div>
 </div>
 </div>
</section>

