<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="sec bg-white relative py-16">
 <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
 <h2 class="text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-black text-slate-900 uppercase italic tracking-tighter mb-10 text-center">TFT Smart Display <span class="text-brandOrange">FAQ</span></h2>
 <div class="space-y-4">
 <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">What does the TFT display show?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">▼</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">The TFT color screen shows real-time battery percentage, current charging/discharging wattage, estimated time remaining, and active port indicators. The display auto-dims after 10 seconds to conserve power.</p>
 </details>
 <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">Is it Qi2 certified?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">▼</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">Yes. Both WOP25 and WOP15 are WPC Qi2 certified with magnetic alignment, delivering 15W wireless charging to compatible iPhones (15 series and newer) and Android devices supporting Qi2.</p>
 </details>
 <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">What is the MOQ for TFT display power bank OEM?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">▼</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">MOQ starts at 500 units for standard models with custom logo printing on the shell. Custom display boot logo or color theme customization requires MOQ 1,000 units. Sample turnaround: 5-7 days.</p>
 </details>
 <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">Can I customize the display boot logo?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">&#9660;</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">Yes. We offer full display customization including custom boot animation/logo, color theme matching to your brand palette, and custom status icons and UI layout. MOQ 1,000 units for display customization. Add 5-7 days to lead time for firmware integration.</p>
 </details>
 <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">What is the difference between LED and TFT display on power banks?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">&#9660;</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">LED displays show only battery percentage as a simple number (single color, no graphics). TFT displays are full-color screens showing real-time wattage, voltage, current, estimated time remaining, and port activity — plus they support custom boot logos and brand themes. TFT costs $1.50-3.00 more per unit but enables $40-100 retail pricing vs $15-30 for LED-only products.</p>
 </details>
 <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">Does the display drain the power bank battery?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">&#9660;</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">Negligibly. The TFT screen auto-dims after 10 seconds and consumes less than 0.1% battery per hour when active. Over a full charge cycle, display power consumption is under 0.5% of total capacity — invisible to end users.</p>
 </details>
 <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">Is a power bank with a display worth it for Amazon sellers?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">&#9660;</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">Yes. Display-equipped power banks command 40-60% higher MSRP than identical-capacity no-display models. They also generate better product photography (the screen looks premium in listings), reduce "doesn't charge" returns (users can see real-time wattage), and differentiate in Amazon's crowded power bank category.</p>
 </details>
